-4c94fcfc-480b-4ecb-80e6-6cc3a652bb38"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"},{"content_hash":"d38b73d16f2e24500e359d7632d872610a20a07a16a8fb51db0d804510e4245e","event_uuid":"caa235c1-cf88-4cc2-ab5a-0f226b62e018","position":{"commit_sha":"9b599a994c1c676d1ce3b7d45f84c12c779409fd","position":"1784265143770327001-caa235c1-cf88-4cc2-ab5a-0f226b62e018"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"},{"content_hash":"adabdd379b7da6d8c723aa7257749302e1bc6e4b2b8f9c39503c522d5688bf32","event_uuid":"0a939464-faab-464e-a676-f97cf6091931","position":{"commit_sha":"26d994d6e69d1ab4f6783707ed4f267e942ade87","position":"1784265145750201001-0a939464-faab-464e-a676-f97cf6091931"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"}],"bridge_alerts":[],"claim_harness":"claude-code_2-1-212_agent","claim_remote_session":null,"claimed_session":"aa9cb5ff-3fdb-44d3-8af8-c125c27f20ad","comments":[{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","body":"Rename + de-brand done (examples/claude-skills -> examples/agent-skills). AC1 (rg -l 'examples/claude-skills' . == 0) note: the ONLY remaining match is docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/runs/adjudication_corpus.jsonl:362 — a FROZEN plan-review eval corpus where 'examples/claude-skills' appears inside a verbatim quoted historical finding (finding_id f0bc77fa9e5c47e8a, decision=dropped). It is historical/eval evidence, NOT a live path reference; rewriting it would falsify the frozen corpus (same principle as the deliberately-excluded CHANGELOG, and sibling 5b01's own sweep excludes docs/experiments). Left untouched by design. No LIVE reference to the old path remains (git grep excl CHANGELOG/experiments = 0).","timestamp":1784254047260373001}],"created_at":1784230962780810001,"creation_channel":"unknown","deps":[{"link_uuid":"1581c3de-1ced-4375-a92c-2fea03386488","relation":"depends_on","target_id":"6642-814b-8bc5-4ff4"}],"description":"# Generalize the example skills: rename claude-skills -> agent-skills and de-brand\n\n## Why\n\nThe example skills already use the SKILL.md format, which is now a cross-provider OPEN standard\n(Anthropic's Agent Skills, adopted by Codex, Copilot, Cursor, Gemini CLI, JetBrains Junie, and\nmore) — so the format is the right portable bet and should be KEPT. What is Claude-locked is the\npackaging: the directory name `examples/claude-skills/`, the README's \"Claude Code\" branding and\ndocs.claude.com link, some Claude-Code-specific phrasing (\"the Task tool\"), and internal\nreferences to `CLAUDE.md`/`CLAUDE.local.md`. Generalizing these makes the examples usable as\nillustrative material for any harness.\n\n## What\n\nRename `examples/claude-skills/` → `examples/agent-skills/`. Update the README to de-brand:\nstate that SKILL.md is a cross-provider standard, note which harnesses read skills and from\nwhere (paths differ per tool), and drop the Claude-only framing. Generalize Claude-Code-specific\norchestration phrasing to provider-neutral wording (\"subagent\" is fine; replace \"the Task tool\"\nand similar). Repoint internal references from `CLAUDE.md`/`CLAUDE.local.md` to `AGENTS.md`.\nUpdate the shared/ sync test (`tests/unit/test_skill_shared_sync.py`) and any code/docs that\nreference the old path, so `make test` stays green. Keep each SKILL.md's `name`/`description`\nfrontmatter (the portable core).\n\n## Scope\n\nIn: `examples/agent-skills/**`, `tests/unit/test_skill_shared_sync.py`, and any references to\nthe old dir path. Out: rewriting the skills' substantive logic. Depends on: the AGENTS.md story\n(so the `CLAUDE.md → AGENTS.md` reference repoint targets the real new file).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Directory renamed to `examples/agent-skills/`; no stale path references remain.\n  - Proving: `rg -l 'examples/claude-skills' . | wc -l` == 0.\n- [ ] README de-branded: no \"Claude Code\"-only framing; states SKILL.md portability and where\n  each harness looks for skills.\n  - Proving: reviewer confirms; `rg -c 'Claude Code' examples/agent-skills/README.md` reduced to\n    only accurate, non-exclusive mentions.\n- [ ] Skill bodies use provider-neutral phrasing and reference `AGENTS.md` (not `CLAUDE.md`).\n  - Proving: `rg -c 'the Task tool|CLAUDE\\.local\\.md' examples/agent-skills/` == 0.\n- [ ] `make lint && make test` pass (shared-sync test updated to the new path).\n\n## De-risking results (exact rename surface)\n\nRenaming `examples/claude-skills` → `examples/agent-skills` is low-risk and CI-safe. Exact\nsurface confirmed by sweep: `tests/unit/test_skill_shared_sync.py` (`SKILLS_DIR` line 25 +\ndocstring lines 3, 9-10) and `examples/claude-skills/README.md:44` (the cp example).\n**No `.github/workflows` reference** — nothing in CI depends on the path. Skill-body `CLAUDE.md`\nreferences to repoint to `AGENTS.md`: `rebar-implement/SKILL.md` and\n`rebar-janitor/phases/discovery.md`. SKILL.md is confirmed as the cross-provider open standard\n(keep the format). The provider-neutral phrasing sweep still applies (drop \"the Task tool\", etc.).","env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","file_impact":[{"path":"examples/agent-skills","reason":"rename+generalize skills dir"},{"path":"tests/unit/test_skill_shared_sync.py","reason":"update shared-sync path"}],"keyring":[],"last_status_env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","managed_refs":[["depends_on","6642-814b-8bc5-4ff4"],["parent","81e2-ad5e-bfe2-4653"]],"parent_id":"81e2-ad5e-bfe2-4653","parent_status_uuid":"caa235c1-cf88-4cc2-ab5a-0f226b62e018","preconditions_summary":{"status":"pre-manifest"},"priority":2,"reverts":[],"status":"closed","tags":[],"ticket_id":"46f8-cd08-7bf5-4508","ticket_type":"story","title":"Generalize the example skills: rename claude-skills -> agent-skills and de-brand","verify_commands":[]},"source_event_uuids":["6e1a4c94-ca84-40ef-a877-e84797721e24","1581c3de-1ced-4375-a92c-2fea03386488","b9673366-1992-4336-885d-53a536423ad8","5e9f683c-a352-4307-b3c6-029ca3c3e24b","106e7bff-d347-40b6-9181-d78f3f142753","bdf9c666-ab8a-4395-a887-9021a2475fba","28b99f32-7699-472e-a995-c77c3daea498","7eab6067-d5e7-4a2f-9635-b58679197118","249a0dd6-d7f0-4d15-9fc8-20d8505bd00e","6dac49c6-04af-45c1-bb67-887302149453","54317197-d3f4-4a04-aa77-490540cdafad","aa6e0bbf-4934-46f1-bca5-60e66b3603cf","4c94fcfc-480b-4ecb-80e6-6cc3a652bb38","caa235c1-cf88-4cc2-ab5a-0f226b62e018","0a939464-faab-464e-a676-f97cf6091931"]},"env_id":"","event_type":"SNAPSHOT","timestamp":1784346955767763001,"uuid":"4d5609a1-3b1f-4a46-94e7-b72506106694"}